# Chronos Agent Rules

Read before creating files or modules:

- `chronos/AGENTS.md` — master agent instructions
- `chronos/PROJECT-CONVENTIONS.md` — folder structure, layer separation
- `chronos/DESIGN-ETHICS.md` — Sunsama-aligned UI standards (required for any UI/landing work)
- `chronos/ROADMAP.md` — current launch phase

## Auth work

Load skills from `chronos/.agents/skills/`:

- `better-auth-best-practices`
- `better-auth-security-best-practices`
- `create-auth-skill`

Reference implementation: `best-practices-flow/apps/backend/src/lib/auth.ts`

## Architecture

- Controllers → Services → Repositories (never skip layers)
- Better Auth at `/api/auth/*`; business API at `/api/*` via Hono
- `userId` filter on every repository query
- Named exports, kebab-case files
- Use yarn, not npm

## UI

Do not change existing UI layout/colors without user approval.
When building new UI (auth pages, landing), follow DESIGN-ETHICS.md.
